      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p> The papers of Joseph Smith Fowler, educator, lawyer, and United
		  States senator from Tennessee, were given to the Library of Congress by
		  Elizabeth Shankland Chandler and Fowler Shankland via Mrs. Jefferson P.
		  Chandler in 1931, by Mrs. William A. Croffut also in 1931, and by Elizabeth
		  Johnston Sneed and Samuel Richards Johnston via John Clement Fitzpatrick in
		  1938.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <processinfo encodinganalog="583">
         <head>Processing History</head>
         <p>The papers of Joseph Smith Fowler were processed in 1987. The finding
		  aid was revised in 2009.</p>
      </processinfo>
