      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p>The papers of Joseph Smith Fowler (1820-1902) span the years 1863-1903
		  and consist of correspondence, biographical material, a memorandum book,
		  writings, printed matter, and other material relating mainly to
		  autobiographical reflections on his political activity as a Unionist and as
		  comptroller of Tennessee under Andrew Johnson during the Civil War and his
		  service from 1866 to 1871 as United States senator from Tennessee. Included are
		  observations on Reconstruction and opposition to the impeachment of President
		  Andrew Johnson.</p>
      </scopecontent>
